==English==

===Etymology===
From [[w:Robert Hooke|Robert Hooke]], English physicist

===Noun phrase===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Hooke's [[law]]'''
#{{physics}} the [[principle]] that the [[stress]] applied to a [[solid]] is directly [[proportional]] to the [[strain]] produced.  This law describes the behavior of [[spring]]s and solids stressed within their [[elastic limit]].
 
